1
00:10:27,980 --> 00:10:33,800
It’s such a great thing to meet your children 
after such a long time.

2
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:43,050
And 
this country was really pestered with cold

3
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:47,890
so I had to come here I think, just to make 
you feel warmer with love.

4
00:10:47,890 --> 00:11:02,210
It’s a very heartening thing to see so many 
people who are in England, who are Sahaj Yogis.

5
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:16,850
As you know England has to do tremendous effort 
to keep Sahaja Yoga afloat; not only that,

6
00:11:16,850 --> 00:11:23,040
but you have to set in examples for others.

7
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:30,320
As England is the heart of the universe it 
circulates.

8
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:33,840
Whatever example you set in, circulates.

9
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,290
People try to follow you.

10
00:11:36,290 --> 00:11:42,490
As I have told you before also, that English 
people should not try to follow other people

11
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:46,600
but establish their own proper character.

12
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:54,640
But not to be insular by which you don’t 
appreciate anybody else or you cannot understand

13
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:57,620
international relationships.

14
00:11:57,620 --> 00:12:13,010
We are one world and it’s only one great 
Viraat in Whose being we circulate.

15
00:12:13,010 --> 00:12:22,340
Moreover for the people who are from the heart, 
[they] have to be much more open and moving

16
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:29,340
and giving because that’s the job of the 
cell of blood that passes through [the] heart;

17
00:12:29,340 --> 00:12:51,190
and that’s how you are made specially for 
this.

18
00:12:51,190 --> 00:12:59,120
I have been speaking after you finished your 
tour on a subject in India.

19
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:05,640
But I think it is more related to us here 
in the West than to Indians.

20
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:14,790
And that is something we have to understand: 
that we are in the midst of terrible conditions,

21
00:13:14,790 --> 00:13:23,150
horrible conditions which are taking us to 
hell.

22
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:41,220
And we realise how important it is for us 
to get together and save this area which we

23
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:44,680
called as ‘the Western world’.

24
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:52,600
So I have already given a little talk which 
you may hear when you have this seminar or

25
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,560
this Shiv puja.

26
00:13:55,560 --> 00:14:06,700
But I would like to tell you about it: that 
Shri Krishna, a long time back, told that

27
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:14,310
the roots of the awareness are in the brain, 
but the human awareness grows downward.

28
00:14:14,310 --> 00:14:20,960
That’s how we have grown downward.

29
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:35,010
We have grown towards things which, if allowed 
to grow that way, may take us away completely

30
00:14:35,010 --> 00:14:36,230
from the roots.

31
00:14:36,230 --> 00:14:46,530
Now if you start the movement, as I said, 
from Bhavasagara, from the evolutionary process,

32
00:14:46,530 --> 00:14:49,560
of going downward.

33
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:59,880
Now in the Bhavasagara that is in the viscera 
of the stomach and all these places, we have

34
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:04,160
a capacity, what we call as of consumption.

35
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:09,850
We can even consume the poison.

36
00:15:09,850 --> 00:15:17,490
The liver can consume the poison; it has the 
capacity to consume the poison as heat and

37
00:15:17,490 --> 00:15:26,290
then it delivers the heat to the water of 
the bloodstream.

38
00:15:26,290 --> 00:15:35,620
So the capacity we have to consume all those 
things makes us, what we call ‘swahaa’:

39
00:15:35,620 --> 00:15:39,910
‘swahaa’ means ‘consumption’.

40
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:46,450
And from this consumption, when we consume 
all these things: we consume our ego, we consume

41
00:15:46,450 --> 00:15:52,080
our conditioning, we consume all those things 
which are detrimental to our growth [then]

42
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:54,090
we become ‘swadhaa’.

43
00:15:54,090 --> 00:15:58,730
‘Swa‘ is the Spirit and ‘dha’ is the 
dharma.

44
00:15:58,730 --> 00:16:04,060
We get the dharma of the Spirit.

45
00:16:04,060 --> 00:16:10,370
And you know what is the dharma of the Spirit 
is – is Sahaj, Sahaja.

46
00:16:10,370 --> 00:16:18,050
But when we start going downward only with 
our awareness, from the Nabhi Chakra we start

47
00:16:18,050 --> 00:16:25,590
moving downward, what happens to us [is] that 
we move to the second position of Swadhishthana

48
00:16:25,590 --> 00:16:31,850
and the Swadhishthana has got the essence, 
I mean, has got the capacity to be ‘bhurvah’.

49
00:16:31,850 --> 00:16:38,440
‘Bhurvah’ means the whole Creation, the 
universe that is created.

50
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:42,550
That’s how we get creativity through Swadhishthana.

51
00:16:42,550 --> 00:16:50,940
So when we start moving downward, what happens 
to us [is] we go to all the stars and the

52
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:55,040
planets and all that are created, that’s 
what we are doing, wasting our energy for

53
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,520
nothing at all.

54
00:16:56,520 --> 00:17:01,330
But apart from that in the wrong way when 
we move, our attention goes to creativity

55
00:17:01,330 --> 00:17:12,990
which is destructive, which is negative, which 
brings death, which suggests insipidness.

56
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:17,260
Like the art today is, when you see the art, 
you don’t know whether to vomit, to run

57
00:17:17,260 --> 00:17:20,550
away or to cry.

58
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:25,550
So that explains why people are producing 
such horrid things and when you look at them

59
00:17:25,550 --> 00:17:29,280
you don’t understand what is this going 
on.

60
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:40,710
So the art, the creativity, in every way, 
the creativity of every kind becomes so horrid.

61
00:17:40,710 --> 00:17:44,270
So the third stage is that we go to ‘bhuh‘.

62
00:17:44,270 --> 00:17:48,380
‘Bhuh’ is this Mother Earth.

63
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:52,900
Mother Earth is the one which also creates 
Shri Ganesh.

64
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:57,980
Now when we go towards Mother Earth we start 
extracting Mother Earth, taking out all that

65
00:17:57,980 --> 00:18:02,780
is precious, that is needed out of proportion 
– because we have got machines.

66
00:18:02,780 --> 00:18:05,090
Now we have got machines so we must produce.

67
00:18:05,090 --> 00:18:11,400
The machine must produce more and more and 
more, out of proportion it should go on.

68
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:17,950
And when it wants to continue it has to go 
on that way so that you feed the machine to

69
00:18:17,950 --> 00:18:23,090
produce more.

70
00:18:23,090 --> 00:18:28,700
Now this production is useless!

71
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:31,060
There is no need to have so much production 
for us.

72
00:18:31,060 --> 00:18:37,390
You see plastics after plastics, then there’s 
nylons after nylons, then there’s all kinds

73
00:18:37,390 --> 00:18:41,810
of polyester and I don’t know all kinds 
of things that they have started producing.

74
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:44,300
All man-made nonsense that they have.

75
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:47,120
There’s no need to have so much.

76
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:52,370
Then we go on accumulating things and that’s 
how we become extremely materialistic people.

77
00:18:52,370 --> 00:18:57,900
Actually to be materialistic in the real sense 
is that we understand the value of matter.

78
00:18:57,900 --> 00:19:00,360
And the value of the matter is aesthetics.

79
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:03,380
Artistic things, real artistic things.

80
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:10,490
And beyond that the value of matter is that 
you can give love to others through that matter:

81
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:14,350
by giving as presents, by your generosity.

82
00:19:14,350 --> 00:19:15,880
So you lose that also!

83
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,420
That power also you lose.

84
00:19:17,420 --> 00:19:25,140
That is, you start extracting your Mother 
Earth in such a way that you don’t know

85
00:19:25,140 --> 00:19:30,600
what to do with the acid gas that is coming 
out of these productions and then all your

86
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,310
trees are getting destroyed.

87
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:33,590
It’s so destructive.

88
00:19:33,590 --> 00:19:36,760
The whole thing is so destructive.

89
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:45,670
So then you move to the essence of Mooladhara 
which is innocence.

90
00:19:45,670 --> 00:19:49,730
And when it is innocence, you start attacking 
innocence.

91
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:51,810
Now you read horrible things, when you come 
here.

92
00:19:51,810 --> 00:19:57,170
I got the jitters when I heard about the six 
year old girl and a three year old girl: I

93
00:19:57,170 --> 00:19:58,170
just can’t bear it.

94
00:19:58,170 --> 00:20:02,800
Supposing that was my child what would have 
happened to me?

95
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:03,800
And it’s my child.

96
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:04,960
That’s how I feel.

97
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:10,680
Then we are attacking the innocence everywhere 
in every place and we have no sense of Mooladhar.

98
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:13,590
That’s how we go down.

99
00:20:13,590 --> 00:20:17,990
And one step forward where do we go?

100
00:20:17,990 --> 00:20:20,370
Into hell.

101
00:20:20,370 --> 00:20:21,370
That is our movement.

102
00:20:21,370 --> 00:20:23,390
We are going towards hell!

103
00:20:23,390 --> 00:20:27,570
Straight forward, our movement is towards 
hell!

104
00:20:27,570 --> 00:20:32,430
Because I have explained in that little talk, 
you can hear it again, that, when you see

105
00:20:32,430 --> 00:20:38,110
the steps, you see the downward steps, then 
you just see the platforms which are very

106
00:20:38,110 --> 00:20:43,750
good, maybe of marble, very attractive, very 
sensational, whatever you may call it.

107
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:47,270
And you feel like going down, it’s easy 
to go down with the gravity because you have

108
00:20:47,270 --> 00:20:56,120
come out from amoeba state or even earlier 
from carbon stage, so you feel it’s easy

109
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,430
to go down.

110
00:20:57,430 --> 00:21:03,820
It’s much easier to go down, so you go on 
stepping on these steps and go down.

111
00:21:03,820 --> 00:21:05,610
You don’t see the heights.

112
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:11,920
But when you are going higher, rising higher 
then you start seeing the heights.

113
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:16,020
And when you see the heights what do you see 
from down below?

114
00:21:16,020 --> 00:21:17,350
Absolutely this is our task.

115
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:20,740
From the hell we have to pull out people up.

116
00:21:20,740 --> 00:21:21,740
That’s hell!

117
00:21:21,740 --> 00:21:25,520
And this is what we call as the ‘adhogati’ 
– going downward.

118
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:27,240
‘Adhogati’ – going downward.

119
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:31,540
We have to take to ‘Urdhvagati’ ( ऊर्ध्वगति)- 
going higher.

120
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,990
How do we go higher?

121
00:21:33,990 --> 00:21:35,860
Only Kundalini is the way.

122
00:21:35,860 --> 00:21:37,730
That you can see clearly.

123
00:21:37,730 --> 00:21:42,830
Even people who try to go higher without the 
Kundalini, say from Nabhi upwards, how do

124
00:21:42,830 --> 00:21:43,830
they do it?

125
00:21:43,830 --> 00:21:50,470
They go up to mana, this is the emotional 
side, that’s the motherhood.

126
00:21:50,470 --> 00:21:52,750
And you go against the mother.

127
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:57,980
When you go there what you find [is] that 
you get attached to this woman, that woman,

128
00:21:57,980 --> 00:21:59,020
then that thing.

129
00:21:59,020 --> 00:22:04,420
It goes on to this family, to other things 
and again you come down.

130
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:10,520
Then you go ahead, you go into ‘janah’ 
– is the one which is what we call ‘the

131
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:11,830
public’, ‘the others’.

132
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:14,480
‘Janah’ is ‘the public’, is the Viraata’s 
place.

133
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,390
As you know this is the Viraata’s place.

134
00:22:16,390 --> 00:22:23,190
And when you go to that place, to Viraata’s 
place, what happens to you [is] that you start

135
00:22:23,190 --> 00:22:26,110
becoming very conscious of yourself, “Oh, 
I am a public man.

136
00:22:26,110 --> 00:22:27,370
I am a public person.

137
00:22:27,370 --> 00:22:28,580
This is my reputation.

138
00:22:28,580 --> 00:22:30,730
I am this and I am that."

139
00:22:30,730 --> 00:22:34,750
And then you start exploiting people with 
your politics and all other things like that.

140
00:22:34,750 --> 00:22:43,440
And you develop your egos; all kinds of nonsensical 
things.

141
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:50,110
With your mana, from your centre heart, you 
develop also your conditionings and that’s

142
00:22:50,110 --> 00:22:56,500
how you develop a funny personality which 
is not urdhvagati, which is not going higher,

143
00:22:56,500 --> 00:23:03,790
but is actually giving you additional problems 
on your back!

144
00:23:03,790 --> 00:23:10,160
Then the third thing is here at the Agnya, 
as I told you, you develop your ego.

145
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:15,540
The other day Patrick rang me up to say, “Mother, 
why are we developing our Agnyas so much nowadays?”

146
00:23:15,540 --> 00:23:18,500
I said, “Stop reading newspapers!”

147
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:23,910
The prime ministers are fighting for their 
seats and this and that and if you read newspapers

148
00:23:23,910 --> 00:23:27,520
you will also feel that you are a prime minister 
[and] you better fight it.

149
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:34,050
Because when you see a picture or any drama 
sometimes you get identified and you think,

150
00:23:34,050 --> 00:23:37,980
“I am Napoleon myself!”

151
00:23:37,980 --> 00:23:41,920
So don’t read newspapers!

152
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:47,710
Don’t read about these mad people who are 
just trying to overpower each other.

153
00:23:47,710 --> 00:23:50,000
Like this [Ferdinand] Marcos fellow.

154
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,460
The other day somebody said that, “Mother, 
you get rid of this Marcos!”

155
00:23:52,460 --> 00:23:53,860
Now he’s out!

156
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:55,990
So many will be out but what about us?

157
00:23:55,990 --> 00:23:58,610
Do we have some of them within our heads?

158
00:23:58,610 --> 00:24:06,040
Do we also have the same ideas of materialism 
or ego or all these trips that these people

159
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:07,890
have had?

160
00:24:07,890 --> 00:24:13,700
So as a result, when you see these things, 
on the contrary, you should try to avoid it

161
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:17,650
and jump on to urdhvagati.

162
00:24:17,650 --> 00:24:22,110
Then you go higher, from there, in the head 
is the Sat, is the Truth.

163
00:24:22,110 --> 00:24:26,660
That’s what you discover, Truth; should 
discover in the normal way.

164
00:24:26,660 --> 00:24:33,790
But in the abnormal conditions when you try 
just to climb up to the brain, what happens

165
00:24:33,790 --> 00:24:40,180
is that whatever you know through your mental 
conception becomes the truth.

166
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:41,180
Everyone is like that.

167
00:24:41,180 --> 00:24:45,060
You see, about religion you will find a person 
believes that, “This is the truth.

168
00:24:45,060 --> 00:24:46,550
Now this is the truth!”

169
00:24:46,550 --> 00:24:53,610
“I am the one who represents Christianity”, 
“I am the one who represents Mohammad Sahib”,

170
00:24:53,610 --> 00:24:59,690
“I am the one who represents Nanak Sahib”, 
“I am the one who represents Shri Rama,

171
00:24:59,690 --> 00:25:01,190
Shri Krishna."

172
00:25:01,190 --> 00:25:02,380
None of them represent.

173
00:25:02,380 --> 00:25:04,350
It’s just a concept.

174
00:25:04,350 --> 00:25:08,680
And with that concept if you move about like 
that then what happens [is] you just get stuck

175
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:10,290
on to that idea.

176
00:25:10,290 --> 00:25:13,390
That is how fanaticism comes in as far as 
religion is concerned.

177
00:25:13,390 --> 00:25:19,910
There are many, many things like that, “This 
is a concept and that’s the fact, and that’s

178
00:25:19,910 --> 00:25:23,180
the truth and that’s what I believe in this!”

179
00:25:23,180 --> 00:25:25,390
But why do you believe in that?

180
00:25:25,390 --> 00:25:27,560
Who are you?

181
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:30,950
When they say, “I believe,” just go and 
ask them, “Who are you after all to believe

182
00:25:30,950 --> 00:25:31,950
in that?”

183
00:25:31,950 --> 00:25:32,950
That’s Mr.

184
00:25:32,950 --> 00:25:34,450
Ego, that’s all.

185
00:25:34,450 --> 00:25:37,370
Then there are people who are conditioned.

186
00:25:37,370 --> 00:25:41,390
And that’s what, whatever is their conditioning, 
they think, “This is the conditioning.

187
00:25:41,390 --> 00:25:42,830
This is the thing I am brought up.

188
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:47,670
This is how I have lived and this is how I 
am, and this is what is the truth."

189
00:25:47,670 --> 00:25:52,400
Both things are absurd, mythical.

190
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:56,180
That’s not the Truth.

191
00:25:56,180 --> 00:26:02,850
So when you start through your urdhvagati, 
through your Kundalini you see the height.

192
00:26:02,850 --> 00:26:04,890
You see that, “Now we have to rise!

193
00:26:04,890 --> 00:26:05,890
We have to rise.

194
00:26:05,890 --> 00:26:06,890
Rise with our innocence.

195
00:26:06,890 --> 00:26:08,250
We have to get to our innocence."

196
00:26:08,250 --> 00:26:12,030
We have to be innocent people.

197
00:26:12,030 --> 00:26:16,610
But even in Sahaja Yoga you will find some 
people, I call them sometimes like monkeys,

198
00:26:16,610 --> 00:26:18,830
jump from urdhvagati to adhogati, adhogati 
to urdhvagati.

199
00:26:18,830 --> 00:26:25,230
You don’t know which side they are going!

200
00:26:25,230 --> 00:26:27,940
You have to hold on to these steps which you 
have got.

201
00:26:27,940 --> 00:26:29,480
First is the innocence.

202
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:35,450
Your morality, as you call that, or a chastity.

203
00:26:35,450 --> 00:26:38,960
That’s the first step you have to achieve.

204
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:45,660
Unless and until you achieve that step how 
are you going to go further?

205
00:26:45,660 --> 00:26:46,740
But it’s the other way round.

206
00:26:46,740 --> 00:26:51,240
They think if you tell something very truthfully 
to Mother, “I have had five love affairs,

207
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:57,270
I have had six abortions, ten this thing, 
then Mother is going to be very happy with

208
00:26:57,270 --> 00:27:00,160
me,” because they have told the truth.

209
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:02,900
That’s not the truth.

210
00:27:02,900 --> 00:27:05,580
That’s not what is wanted.

211
00:27:05,580 --> 00:27:07,280
Are you now a chaste person?

212
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:13,890
Have you got the ideas of chastity and dharma?

213
00:27:13,890 --> 00:27:17,450
That is the second step you can move into.

214
00:27:17,450 --> 00:27:23,210
Aesthetically, are you rich aesthetically, 
are you generous?

215
00:27:23,210 --> 00:27:26,690
Can you appreciate the art of every country?

216
00:27:26,690 --> 00:27:30,160
Or you just say, “Oh it’s not good because 
it’s not English!”?

217
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:32,620
Or “It’s not good because it’s not French!”?

218
00:27:32,620 --> 00:27:34,440
Or maybe, “It’s not from Wimbledon!”

219
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:38,340
Could come to that point!

220
00:27:38,340 --> 00:27:40,830
I mean, what is happening to us?

221
00:27:40,830 --> 00:27:49,290
We are becoming so insular, so small, so narrow 
in our outlook, that’s impossible.

222
00:27:49,290 --> 00:27:52,470
We cannot appreciate another person at all.

223
00:27:52,470 --> 00:27:57,200
You ask anyone, everybody has an opinion about 
others, what about yourself?

224
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:59,540
What is your opinion about yourself?

