don’t do anything.

621
00:56:50,580 --> 00:56:51,580
It’s a myth.

622
00:56:51,580 --> 00:56:52,580
It’s just a myth.

623
00:56:52,580 --> 00:56:53,580
“I don’t forgive."

624
00:56:53,580 --> 00:56:54,580
Means what do you do?

625
00:56:54,580 --> 00:56:55,580
It’s a myth.

626
00:56:55,580 --> 00:57:09,950
New Lady: It’s how you feel towards a person 
who has committed so many crimes and the detention

627
00:57:09,950 --> 00:57:11,330
of Jews.

628
00:57:11,330 --> 00:57:15,430
Shri Mataji: But what about Jewish now?

629
00:57:15,430 --> 00:57:19,180
If they had forgiven Hitler, God would have 
looked after him!

630
00:57:19,180 --> 00:57:20,310
God is looking after him.

631
00:57:20,310 --> 00:57:24,550
But when the Jews didn’t forgive him, they 
have become more like Hitler, sometimes.

632
00:57:24,550 --> 00:57:27,410
They behave like Hitler sometimes I feel.

633
00:57:27,410 --> 00:57:30,780
The way they are treating PLO people is something 
horrible.

634
00:57:30,780 --> 00:57:36,770
You see, so if you do not forgive you become 
like the person you are hating.

635
00:57:36,770 --> 00:57:38,810
If you forgive you don’t become like that.

636
00:57:38,810 --> 00:57:40,840
Just that person goes out of your mind completely.

637
00:57:40,840 --> 00:57:43,510
I mean, they have imbibed certain qualities 
now.

638
00:57:43,510 --> 00:57:46,490
I can’t imagine Jews behaving like this!

639
00:57:46,490 --> 00:57:49,400
They are behaving in a very funny manner.

640
00:57:49,400 --> 00:57:50,920
You can see it clearly!

641
00:57:50,920 --> 00:57:58,810
I mean, they had no place to go, they had 
no land to live, they were given a land.

642
00:57:58,810 --> 00:58:02,560
And now the way they are troubling PLOs, I 
was amazed.

643
00:58:02,560 --> 00:58:06,710
Because I met some of the students of this 
PLO people who came to India, who have been

644
00:58:06,710 --> 00:58:07,960
given asylum.

645
00:58:07,960 --> 00:58:13,480
And when I heard how Jews tortured them – just 
like Hitler, just like Hitler.

646
00:58:13,480 --> 00:58:16,340
I wish they had forgiven.

647
00:58:16,340 --> 00:58:21,430
I mean, if they had not forgiven Hitler, what 
did they do out of it?

648
00:58:21,430 --> 00:58:22,430
Nothing!

649
00:58:22,430 --> 00:58:24,010
Hitler is punished by God, not by you.

650
00:58:24,010 --> 00:58:26,530
What can you punish him?

651
00:58:26,530 --> 00:58:29,980
You cannot punish him.

652
00:58:29,980 --> 00:58:32,850
Alright?

653
00:58:32,850 --> 00:58:36,530
When we forgive, we don’t imbibe that cruelty 
within ourselves.

654
00:58:36,530 --> 00:58:38,470
That’s the biggest thing that happens.

655
00:58:38,470 --> 00:58:44,700
Apart from that we do not suffer when we forgive.

656
00:58:44,700 --> 00:58:54,540
I mean, if you go on thinking about it, what 
people did say, imagine, think of the people

657
00:58:54,540 --> 00:58:55,540
when Mr.

658
00:58:55,540 --> 00:58:59,310
Columbus reached America, who followed them 
[and] what they did there!

659
00:58:59,310 --> 00:59:00,390
Horrible things.

660
00:59:00,390 --> 00:59:03,060
I mean, worse than Hitler.

661
00:59:03,060 --> 00:59:07,490
They wiped out each and every person from 
there.

662
00:59:07,490 --> 00:59:12,500
Then when they tried to consume other countries, 
going to other countries and ruling them.

663
00:59:12,500 --> 00:59:16,230
If you go to China you will be shocked, even 
about English, what they have to say.

664
00:59:16,230 --> 00:59:18,280
Even in India, if you go, you will find.

665
00:59:18,280 --> 00:59:23,460
How can anybody forgive them if you think 
what they have done?

666
00:59:23,460 --> 00:59:28,500
But that is finished now and gone, forever!

667
00:59:28,500 --> 00:59:31,840
You are not to think about it at all.

668
00:59:31,840 --> 00:59:32,890
It’s finished.

669
00:59:32,890 --> 00:59:36,020
Today, what is the situation, we have to see.

670
00:59:36,020 --> 00:59:42,680
You will be amazed, if I tell you, that myself, 
I was tortured by English very much.

671
00:59:42,680 --> 00:59:43,680
So what?

672
00:59:43,680 --> 00:59:45,210
For me you are my children.

673
00:59:45,210 --> 00:59:47,760
I don’t think of that at all because that’s 
finished.

674
00:59:47,760 --> 00:59:50,070
They were bhootish people, that’s all – finished.

675
00:59:50,070 --> 00:59:51,070
Where are they?

676
00:59:51,070 --> 00:59:52,380
Where is Hitler today?

677
00:59:52,380 --> 00:59:54,710
Where are those people who died?

678
00:59:54,710 --> 00:59:55,710
Finished!

679
00:59:55,710 --> 01:00:00,800
Better to forgive so that God punishes them 
well.

680
01:00:00,800 --> 01:00:07,040
Now, today, is not the time of punishing anyone, 
it’s the time of evolving, of helping people

681
01:00:07,040 --> 01:00:08,440
to rise above that.

682
01:00:08,440 --> 01:00:12,590
So there is no more danger of getting any 
Hitlers on this Earth.

683
01:00:12,590 --> 01:00:14,530
We have to create such a beautiful garden!

684
01:00:14,530 --> 01:00:17,360
Why to think of the thorns?

685
01:00:17,360 --> 01:00:20,990
Forget about all that nonsense, you see!

686
01:00:20,990 --> 01:00:27,600
These are special blossom times: let us think 
of the flowers and not of the past and the

687
01:00:27,600 --> 01:00:30,670
thorns that we had finished off.

688
01:00:30,670 --> 01:00:34,710
We have to give something very beautiful to 
our children.

689
01:00:34,710 --> 01:00:35,770
Isn’t it?

690
01:00:35,770 --> 01:00:38,820
A heritage where people will say, “Oh, I 
see.

691
01:00:38,820 --> 01:00:46,540
There were people who forgave all such things 
and created a beautiful world for us!”

692
01:00:46,540 --> 01:00:52,990
Isn’t it a nice thought?

693
01:00:52,990 --> 01:00:56,340
Better than not forgiving.

694
01:00:56,340 --> 01:01:02,390
Like that we go on thinking about, “He did 
this and he did that."

695
01:01:02,390 --> 01:01:03,910
There’s no end to it!

696
01:01:03,910 --> 01:01:05,170
God looks after!

697
01:01:05,170 --> 01:01:06,170
He’ll punish.

698
01:01:06,170 --> 01:01:07,840
He’s punished him so badly.

699
01:01:07,840 --> 01:01:09,850
Now nobody wants to take Hitler’s name!

700
01:01:09,850 --> 01:01:15,310
I mean, if somebody sees Hitler’s photograph 
somewhere he will go and have a bath in India.

701
01:01:15,310 --> 01:01:19,270
He’ll just go to the river Ganges and have 
a bath, “Oh God!

702
01:01:19,270 --> 01:01:25,310
How did I see Hitler’s face anywhere?”

703
01:01:25,310 --> 01:01:33,020
What more you want as a punishment for Hitler 
that they can ’t even face his photograph?

704
01:01:33,020 --> 01:01:37,810
And some person who looks like Hitler, they’ll 
say, “You just shave off your moustache

705
01:01:37,810 --> 01:01:39,640
at least!

706
01:01:39,640 --> 01:01:43,280
Don’t look like that.

707
01:01:43,280 --> 01:01:46,010
It’s very inauspicious!”

708
01:01:46,010 --> 01:01:50,860
Yes, I know somebody who looked like Hitler 
and they said, “You shave off your moustache

709
01:01:50,860 --> 01:01:55,090
and comb your hair from the other side, or 
make it a parting in the centre.

710
01:01:55,090 --> 01:02:01,840
We can’t see you like this early in the 
morning!”

711
01:02:01,840 --> 01:02:02,840
Imagine!

712
01:02:02,840 --> 01:02:08,590
What an inauspicious face! (laughter) He’s 
hated by anyone.

713
01:02:08,590 --> 01:02:10,450
You go to any place.

714
01:02:10,450 --> 01:02:12,040
Even in Germany they hate him.

715
01:02:12,040 --> 01:02:19,940
So what’s the use of such a character being 
so much dominant on our heads?

716
01:02:19,940 --> 01:02:22,040
Have nothing to do with it.

717
01:02:22,040 --> 01:02:26,300
Because once you start thinking about him 
you also develop certain habits that he had.

718
01:02:26,300 --> 01:02:31,980
A little cruelty comes up when you become 
angry and when you cannot forgive others,

719
01:02:31,980 --> 01:02:34,760
you also think it’s right that you can punish 
others.

720
01:02:34,760 --> 01:02:38,270
Here we are not fighting the sword with a 
sword but with a shield.

721
01:02:38,270 --> 01:02:42,490
We are fighting the sword with a shield.

722
01:02:42,490 --> 01:02:50,760
We never fight sword with a sword, we fight 
it with a shield.

723
01:02:50,760 --> 01:02:58,170
That’s a wise attitude towards life, I think.

724
01:02:58,170 --> 01:03:00,110
Otherwise you will create more Hitlers.

725
01:03:00,110 --> 01:03:03,260
One Hitler is dead and now ten Hitlers have 
come out – already have come out!

726
01:03:03,260 --> 01:03:13,590
They are all to be finished now, once [and] 
for all.

727
01:03:13,590 --> 01:03:38,250
You can help by creating a new pattern, a 
new world of beauty.

728
01:03:38,250 --> 01:03:39,260
Any other question please?

729
01:03:39,260 --> 01:03:43,860
That’s a nice question, I know it happens 
to her.

730
01:03:43,860 --> 01:03:48,240
But now you are feeling better inside aren’t 
you?

731
01:03:48,240 --> 01:03:50,050
(laughing) Much more!

732
01:03:50,050 --> 01:03:52,850
That’s how we have to bring peace on this 
Earth.

733
01:03:52,850 --> 01:03:59,290
How are we going to bring peace if there’s 
still lurking anger?

734
01:03:59,290 --> 01:04:02,570
Not forgiving means anger!

735
01:04:02,570 --> 01:04:07,550
That’s all.

736
01:04:07,550 --> 01:04:10,040
Hmmm.

737
01:04:10,040 --> 01:04:15,020
What else?

738
01:04:15,020 --> 01:04:18,750
Ask some questions at least!

739
01:04:18,750 --> 01:04:20,860
Must ask some questions.

740
01:04:20,860 --> 01:04:23,210
Yes, what’s that doctor?

741
01:04:23,210 --> 01:04:24,250
Dr.

742
01:04:24,250 --> 01:04:39,930
Brian Wells: Shri Mataji, sometimes in my 
work I find myself getting very angry with

743
01:04:39,930 --> 01:04:47,310
the people I work with is this ever appropriate 
or should one always try and love and forgive

744
01:04:47,310 --> 01:04:48,310
them and be gentle.

745
01:04:48,310 --> 01:04:49,310
Shri Mataji: Yes, better try that! (laughter) 
As far as possible!

746
01:04:49,310 --> 01:04:50,310
But sometimes anger can also help.

747
01:04:50,310 --> 01:04:54,200
But I think, just now, for us, we are developing 
now, it’s better to take to the more gentler

748
01:04:54,200 --> 01:04:57,560
ways and things like that and not to get angry 
– for the time being.

749
01:04:57,560 --> 01:04:59,880
But we’ll have to show anger sometimes.

750
01:04:59,880 --> 01:05:02,660
Let God show the anger.

751
01:05:02,660 --> 01:05:05,450
Let him take the credit.

752
01:05:05,450 --> 01:05:10,840
You will be more effective if you are gentle, 
I tell you.

753
01:05:10,840 --> 01:05:19,450
By anger you cannot correct people, you cannot 
make them more efficient; but by love.

754
01:05:19,450 --> 01:05:23,580
Those days are gone where anger and hot-temper 
used to impress people.

755
01:05:23,580 --> 01:05:28,020
Nowadays these people don’t like such people.

756
01:05:28,020 --> 01:05:32,170
Anger or some people are also very silly.

757
01:05:32,170 --> 01:05:36,890
They think [that] by being silly they’ll 
impress others: like clowns or something.

758
01:05:36,890 --> 01:05:37,930
It’s not so.

759
01:05:37,930 --> 01:05:44,790
Now we are different people in this world 
and they just know that this is a silly person,

760
01:05:44,790 --> 01:05:46,460
that’s all.

761
01:05:46,460 --> 01:05:52,820
They expect a leader or anybody who has to 
give something to others has to be something

762
01:05:52,820 --> 01:06:02,910
of a higher and a better personality – it’s 
expected.

763
01:06:02,910 --> 01:06:13,740
Cheapish things or anything that is publicly 
people may like you to do, it a leader does

764
01:06:13,740 --> 01:06:18,690
that they don’t like it, they don’t like 
it.

765
01:06:18,690 --> 01:06:25,100
A leader is supposed to be something above, 
above the normal.

766
01:06:25,100 --> 01:06:29,670
But the idea of leadership these days is alright: 
everybody is doing the ‘shake’ so the

767
01:06:29,670 --> 01:06:30,770
leader is doing the shake.

768
01:06:30,770 --> 01:06:36,850
Then everybody wears a tight jean [so] the 
leader also wears the tight jean and he can’t

769
01:06:36,850 --> 01:06:38,550
sit on his chair!

770
01:06:38,550 --> 01:06:40,390
So that’s not the way.

771
01:06:40,390 --> 01:06:43,700
That’s not the way you can be leaders.

772
01:06:43,700 --> 01:06:47,540
A leader has to make a pattern of his own.

773
01:06:47,540 --> 01:06:51,710
And he doesn’t have to solve the problems 
of the people but give them the problem to

774
01:06:51,710 --> 01:06:52,710
be solved.

775
01:06:52,710 --> 01:06:54,280
That’s how leadership works out.

776
01:06:54,280 --> 01:06:59,810
So for anybody who wants to get anything done, 
must learn that the pattern should be of such

777
01:06:59,810 --> 01:07:09,270
a level that others should not take advantage, 
should not think that they can bring you to

778
01:07:09,270 --> 01:07:10,270
your level.

779
01:07:10,270 --> 01:07:15,360
For example, I’ll tell you: in India there’s 
a habit of eating tobacco, dried tobacco.

780
01:07:15,360 --> 01:07:21,860
Now, those people who eat tobacco, say there’s 
a high court judge – he’ll call his peon

781
01:07:21,860 --> 01:07:30,860
and ask him “Have you go the…”, they 
call it ‘dubbi’ means a small little pouch,

782
01:07:30,860 --> 01:07:36,090
so, “Have you got the dubbi?”

783
01:07:36,090 --> 01:07:39,050
So, the whole dignity is finished!

784
01:07:39,050 --> 01:07:41,360
Whole dignity is finished!

785
01:07:41,360 --> 01:07:46,300
That, just an ordinary peon can say, “Do 
you want your dubbi?”

786
01:07:46,300 --> 01:07:48,720
So then it’s done.

787
01:07:48,720 --> 01:07:54,600
What about his great position and dress and 
everything?

788
01:07:54,600 --> 01:08:02,140
He makes a big gown and wears [and] on the 
head they wear a kind of a wig.

789
01:08:02,140 --> 01:08:14,010
And all that is useless because you are asking 
for a dubbi from a peon!

790
01:08:14,010 --> 01:08:22,860
So what impresses people is dignity, balance, 
poise, humility and truthfulness – straightforward

791
01:08:22,860 --> 01:08:27,790
truthfulness – even in day to day work.

792
01:08:27,790 --> 01:08:34,330
Of course efficiency comes like that.

793
01:08:34,330 --> 01:08:39,070
Peacemaking.

794
01:08:39,070 --> 01:08:41,770
You must make peace between two persons, ten 
persons.

795
01:08:41,770 --> 01:08:46,410
Try to make peace instead of supporting one 
person or taking sides.

796
01:08:46,410 --> 01:08:48,330
Best is to make peace.

797
01:08:48,330 --> 01:08:59,100
But if somebody is doing absolutely wrong, 
then you have to take another attitude.

798
01:08:59,100 --> 01:09:00,720
Any other question?

799
01:09:00,720 --> 01:09:02,130
Yes?

800
01:09:02,130 --> 01:09:04,950
Yogini: (unclear)

801
01:09:04,950 --> 01:09:11,990
Shri Mataji: What’s she saying?

802
01:09:11,990 --> 01:09:22,830
Yogi: She’s asking you to tell us how we 
settle down in Sahaja Yoga.

803
01:09:22,830 --> 01:09:23,830
For the new people.

804
01:09:23,830 --> 01:09:24,830
Shri Mataji: Settle down in Sahaja Yoga?

805
01:09:24,830 --> 01:09:25,830
You are already settled!

806
01:09:25,830 --> 01:09:38,070
Gavin Brown: Some of the new people have come 
quite new to Sahaja Yoga, they haven’t met

807
01:09:38,070 --> 01:09:39,070
you before Mother.

808
01:09:39,070 --> 01:09:46,460
Shri Mataji: You see, I was born so settled 
down I don’t know! (laughter) First of all,

809
01:09:46,460 --> 01:09:53,260
in Sahaja Yoga, one has to realise that you 
have got vibrations.

810
01:09:53,260 --> 01:09:55,500
Now, put it on that.

811
01:09:55,500 --> 01:09:57,230
I think that’s the best criteria.

812
01:09:57,230 --> 01:10:01,290
“Am I getting my vibrations alright?

813
01:10:01,290 --> 01:10:02,560
Are they flowing alright?

814
01:10:02,560 --> 01:10:04,830
If not, what’s wrong with me?”

815
01:10:04,830 --> 01:10:07,580
Direct your attention to yourself to find 
out.

816
01:10:07,580 --> 01:10:10,880
“Is there anything wrong with me that I 
cannot get my vibrations alright?

817
01:10:10,880 --> 01:10:11,880
Alright!

818
01:10:11,880 --> 01:10:13,540
There must be something wrong.

819
01:10:13,540 --> 01:10:14,800
Now what is that wrong?”

820
01:10:14,800 --> 01:10:16,220
Try to correct it.

821
01:10:16,220 --> 01:10:20,070
First of all they must direct their attention 
to themselves then they will start settling

822
01:10:20,070 --> 01:10:21,070
down.

823
01:10:21,070 --> 01:10:25,000
But all the time, supposing, I have seen many 
people who come to Sahaja Yoga: out of them

824
01:10:25,000 --> 01:10:28,490
some say, “I saw one Sahaja Yogi who was 
like this!”

825
01:10:28,490 --> 01:10:32,420
They see to others: how they are are, how 
they are, how they are.

826
01:10:32,420 --> 01:10:37,520
You should see to yourself because this is 
for your benevolence, for your betterment.

827
01:10:37,520 --> 01:10:41,560
So the first attitude should be, “What have 
I gained?

828
01:10:41,560 --> 01:10:43,800
What have I to gain?

829
01:10:43,800 --> 01:10:47,190
How am I to get better?”

830
01:10:47,190 --> 01:10:53,010
Or else there could be some people who think 
that, “I must get better.

831
01:10:53,010 --> 01:10:54,180
My health should be alright.

832
01:10:54,180 --> 01:10:59,670
I didn’t get kshema, benevolence, as was 
promised by Sahaja Yogis!”

833
01:10:59,670 --> 01:11:03,140
No, something wrong with you: still the yoga 
is not established.

834
01:11:03,140 --> 01:11:04,770
First establish your yoga.

835
01:11:04,770 --> 01:11:10,340
If you have not established your yoga how 
can you get what you want?

836
01:11:10,340 --> 01:11:13,180
So, first of all it’s such a genuine effort.

837
01:11:13,180 --> 01:11:17,240
One has to be absolutely genuinely asking 
for that yoga.

838
01:11:17,240 --> 01:11:19,350
And you cannot force people.

839
01:11:19,350 --> 01:11:21,440
You cannot force it.

840
01:11:21,440 --> 01:11:22,440
Whatever lecture you may give.

841
01:11:22,440 --> 01:11:27,040
You may like my lectures or anything, they 
might sound very good but it doesn’t matter.

842
01:11:27,040 --> 01:11:29,570
It must go into your being.

843
01:11:29,570 --> 01:11:31,660
It must work out in your being.

844
01:11:31,660 --> 01:11:33,110
You have to become something.

845
01:11:33,110 --> 01:11:35,360
You should certify yourself that, “Yes, 
yes.

846
01:11:35,360 --> 01:11:38,080
I am like that."

847
01:11:38,080 --> 01:11:40,090
We may be very few – doesn’t matter.

848
01:11:40,090 --> 01:11:41,090
It’s meant for the few.

849
01:11:41,090 --> 01:11:47,610
It cannot be given to every funny type of 
a person or a person who is just forced into

850
01:11:47,610 --> 01:11:48,610
Sahaja Yoga.

851
01:11:48,610 --> 01:11:49,610
You cannot force it.

852
01:11:49,610 --> 01:11:55,570
It’s not like winning over election, you 
see, that you make somebody a communist and

853
01:11:55,570 --> 01:11:57,290
overnight he becomes a capitalist.

854
01:11:57,290 --> 01:11:59,720
It’s not like that.

855
01:11:59,720 --> 01:12:01,430
It’s the inner growth.

856
01:12:01,430 --> 01:12:08,680
And only those who are deserving, who have 
that value of their own existence – only

857
01:12:08,680 --> 01:12:10,380
such people can come.

858
01:12:10,380 --> 01:12:13,130
So you cannot force on them at all!

859
01:12:13,130 --> 01:12:14,590
They have to see to it.

860
01:12:14,590 --> 01:12:18,580
And what they have to see in other people 
[is] that what are they doing that they are

861
01:12:18,580 --> 01:12:19,990
so much settled.

862
01:12:19,990 --> 01:12:24,390
And there should be an understanding that 
we have just now entered into the university,

863
01:12:24,390 --> 01:12:28,140
say for example: a new class we are in.

864
01:12:28,140 --> 01:12:30,860
Now how are we to go higher and higher?

865
01:12:30,860 --> 01:12:33,190
Their attitude has to be that way.

866
01:12:33,190 --> 01:12:35,070
You cannot force things into them.

867
01:12:35,070 --> 01:12:39,490
It’s like I always say [that] I have cooked 
for you, the food is ready.

868
01:12:39,490 --> 01:12:41,160
If you are hungry you will eat it.

869
01:12:41,160 --> 01:12:43,890
I cannot force the food into your mouth!

870
01:12:43,890 --> 01:12:45,630
You have to taste it yourself and enjoy.

871
01:12:45,630 --> 01:12:51,930
But there’s a gap, gap between when they 
get Realisation and when they feel joy because

872
01:12:51,930 --> 01:12:56,430
specially in the West they have no idea as 
to what Realisation is, they have never known

873
01:12:56,430 --> 01:12:57,430
the Kundalini.

874
01:12:57,430 --> 01:13:02,650
It’s a new language to them, everything 
is new, so they have to be given little assistance

875
01:13:02,650 --> 01:13:06,480
and help to tell them that, “No, there is 
joy!

876
01:13:06,480 --> 01:13:07,480
You have to go beyond.

877
01:13:07,480 --> 01:13:10,060
You have to see [that] these things exist.

878
01:13:10,060 --> 01:13:11,640
Whatever the saints have said is true.

879
01:13:11,640 --> 01:13:15,570
Whatever the scriptures have described is 
true and you can find out.

880
01:13:15,570 --> 01:13:17,780
But you have to have patience with yourself."

881
01:13:17,780 --> 01:13:21,950
But if they want to criticise and they want 
to say, “Oh, how can that be?

882
01:13:21,950 --> 01:13:22,950
And how can that be?”

883
01:13:22,950 --> 01:13:25,850
Such people will take too much time!

884
01:13:25,850 --> 01:13:28,250
But there must be some genuine seekers.

885
01:13:28,250 --> 01:13:33,920
And there are some slow movers also so accordingly 
they move and you cannot force them.

886
01:13:33,920 --> 01:13:40,110
At the most you can support them for a while 
but then again they drop down.

887
01:13:40,110 --> 01:13:41,110
You have seen that.

888
01:13:41,110 --> 01:13:46,030
It’s happening every time in the West specially, 
not in India.

889
01:13:46,030 --> 01:13:47,030
Not in India.

890
01:13:47,030 --> 01:13:48,180
Not that, also, in [Indian] villages – it 
doesn’t happen.

891
01:13:48,180 --> 01:13:51,710
Once you get six thousand you get six thousand 
– finished!

892
01:13:51,710 --> 01:13:53,090
I have known least of them.

893
01:13:53,090 --> 01:13:55,550
I don’t know who they are [but] they are 
there.

894
01:13:55,550 --> 01:13:59,800
You meet them somewhere and they’ll just 
come and fall at my feet and say, “Mother

895
01:13:59,800 --> 01:14:01,350
I am a Sahaja Yogi."

896
01:14:01,350 --> 01:14:04,560
I said, “I know that.

897
01:14:04,560 --> 01:14:05,560
I know you are.

898
01:14:05,560 --> 01:14:10,560
You are my children I know just from your 
presence I know you are my children."

899
01:14:10,560 --> 01:14:13,380
So they have to become that.

900
01:14:13,380 --> 01:14:14,400
You cannot force.

901
01:14:14,400 --> 01:14:16,460
That’s one thing we do not realise.

902
01:14:16,460 --> 01:14:26,140
You see, now, in the churches they are compromising, 
“Let’s have a disco dance!

903
01:14:26,140 --> 01:14:34,280
And in the disco dance when the people will 
come then we will have some Christians there."

904
01:14:34,280 --> 01:14:35,280
Imagine!

905
01:14:35,280 --> 01:14:40,660
People who are going to disco dance how can 
they be Christians?

906
01:14:40,660 --> 01:14:45,890
And this kind of a compromise is there because 
it’s a money-oriented stuff.

907
01:14:45,890 --> 01:14:47,790
It is not God-oriented, it’s money-oriented.

908
01:14:47,790 --> 01:14:51,830
So, “We must have more people so that we 
have more money so we can have more clergies,

909
01:14:51,830 --> 01:14:52,940
we can give more pay."

910
01:14:52,940 --> 01:14:55,350
It’s all on that level [that] it works.

911
01:14:55,350 --> 01:14:57,180
But not in Sahaja Yoga.

912
01:14:57,180 --> 01:15:03,200
In Sahaja Yoga everyone is a temple of God, 
everyone is a church of God and everyone has

913
01:15:03,200 --> 01:15:04,590
to come up to that.

914
01:15:04,590 --> 01:15:09,430
And those who do not have that respect of 
oneself, we cannot force.

915
01:15:09,430 --> 01:15:11,950
How can you say, “You must have respect 
for yourself!”

916
01:15:11,950 --> 01:15:13,360
Can you say like that?

917
01:15:13,360 --> 01:15:16,800
I mean, it’s something not possible.

918
01:15:16,800 --> 01:15:19,830
That’s what you all people should know.

919
01:15:19,830 --> 01:15:22,760
Also we should reconcile to that.

920
01:15:22,760 --> 01:15:25,170
I have done my level best.

921
01:15:25,170 --> 01:15:30,460
Except for standing on my head I have done 
everything that is possible but what I find

922
01:15:30,460 --> 01:15:32,350
is that it’s very difficult.

923
01:15:32,350 --> 01:15:33,350
Too much of ego!

924
01:15:33,350 --> 01:15:34,350
Too much.

925
01:15:34,350 --> 01:15:38,090
Too much of ego in the West – absolutely 
– and they are so ignorant.

926
01:15:38,090 --> 01:15:41,010
They have never heard the name of Kundalini, 
can you imagine?

927
01:15:41,010 --> 01:15:43,140
What tremendous ignorance there is.

928
01:15:43,140 --> 01:15:48,850
But those who are wise, those who have pure 
intelligence, came to Sahaja Yoga, they learnt

929
01:15:48,850 --> 01:15:50,400
everything, they know so much.

930
01:15:50,400 --> 01:15:57,350
And some of the Sahaja Yogis in the West know 
more than Indians know, I know.

931
01:15:57,350 --> 01:16:01,890
We can say that there are many good Indian 
Sahaja Yogis but there are some excellent

932
01:16:01,890 --> 01:16:04,060
ones in the West.

933
01:16:04,060 --> 01:16:09,990
Par excellence, I should say, some of them 
are.

934
01:16:09,990 --> 01:16:13,060
So that’s it.

935
01:16:13,060 --> 01:16:14,060
So why worry?

936
01:16:14,060 --> 01:16:21,560
We have the quality, if not the quantity.

937
01:16:21,560 --> 01:16:25,860
But this quality only is going to attract 
these ego people.

938
01:16:25,860 --> 01:16:28,260
That’s only going to attract them, nothing 
else.

939
01:16:28,260 --> 01:16:32,810
This quality of your personality, of your 
temperament, of your behaviour, everything

940
01:16:32,810 --> 01:16:34,210
is going to attract them.

941
01:16:34,210 --> 01:16:41,560
But supposing tomorrow you say, “Alright, 
I’ll make a holey jeans,” and walk about

942
01:16:41,560 --> 01:16:52,490
with the holes in the jeans and then people 
will say, “What a nice Sahaja Yogi he is!”

943
01:16:52,490 --> 01:16:56,000
It’s not the way!

944
01:16:56,000 --> 01:16:58,970
You must have your own personality, you must 
have your own dignity.

945
01:16:58,970 --> 01:17:01,130
You shouldn’t behave like them.

946
01:17:01,130 --> 01:17:03,230
But you should not condemn them either.

947
01:17:03,230 --> 01:17:04,250
Know that they are ignorant.

948
01:17:04,250 --> 01:17:05,250
They have no idea.

949
01:17:05,250 --> 01:17:08,140
They don’t have the knowledge of the roots 
at all.

950
01:17:08,140 --> 01:17:17,730
You have the knowledge, so you have to be 
kind like a teacher is kind to his students.

951
01:17:17,730 --> 01:17:21,760
I never expected that in the West I’ll be 
able to talk to so many people myself.

952
01:17:21,760 --> 01:17:29,110
I mean, in the beginning when I came here 
they used to say, “This Victorian old woman!”

953
01:17:29,110 --> 01:17:30,980
And all kinds of things they branded me with.

954
01:17:30,980 --> 01:17:31,980
So it’s alright.

955
01:17:31,980 --> 01:17:32,980
I didn’t mind that time.

956
01:17:32,980 --> 01:17:34,500
Now they are alright.

957
01:17:34,500 --> 01:17:38,310
That’s how they are, what can you do?

958
01:17:38,310 --> 01:17:42,150
To begin with they brand you, they do this 
and do that.

959
01:17:42,150 --> 01:17:43,150
Hmm.

960
01:17:43,150 --> 01:17:46,580
Any other question?

961
01:17:46,580 --> 01:17:53,400
But the society you can form and get to people 
who believe in a proper life, a healthy life

962
01:17:53,400 --> 01:17:55,480
and healthy society.

963
01:17:55,480 --> 01:17:59,780
You can start a society like that, saying 
that, “We want to belong to the healthy

964
01:17:59,780 --> 01:18:00,780
society."

965
01:18:00,780 --> 01:18:02,460
You can take your children to that kind of 
a thing.

966
01:18:02,460 --> 01:18:05,950
You can get other children: where there are 
no drugs and things like that.

967
01:18:05,950 --> 01:18:07,790
You can start on that level.

968
01:18:07,790 --> 01:18:12,820
Maybe from there you might get some people.

969
01:18:12,820 --> 01:18:20,210
Anything else?

970
01:18:20,210 --> 01:18:38,900
Gavin Brown: Shri Mataji, whenever you speak 
the questions go away!

971
01:18:38,900 --> 01:18:41,350
Shri Mataji: You jump into thoughtless awareness, 
I know that.

972
01:18:41,350 --> 01:18:50,710
Gavin Brown: There’s one thing we’d like 
to ask you is to accept your birthday present

973
01:18:50,710 --> 01:18:51,710
a little early.

974
01:18:51,710 --> 01:18:52,710
Shri Mataji: A birthday present?

975
01:18:52,710 --> 01:19:01,020
I mean if you have so many birthdays I’ll 
become older very fast! (laughter)

976
01:19:01,020 --> 01:19:03,680
Oh, Gavin.

977
01:19:03,680 --> 01:19:06,350
So sweet!

978
01:19:06,350 --> 01:19:13,000
Gavin Brown: Something very little.

979
01:19:13,000 --> 01:19:18,610
Shri Mataji: You always say so!

980
01:19:18,610 --> 01:19:22,160
Thank you very much.

981
01:19:22,160 --> 01:19:23,930
Thank you.

982
01:19:23,930 --> 01:19:36,360
(applause) You better open and show them, 
I don’t know what it is like.

983
01:19:36,360 --> 01:20:09,180
They’ll be very happy to see that.

984
01:20:09,180 --> 01:20:13,460
Those who have got Left Vishuddhi, I would 
suggest you sit down with your left hand towards

985
01:20:13,460 --> 01:20:17,390
me and one hand on the Mother Earth – will 
solve the problem immediately.

986
01:20:17,390 --> 01:20:20,970
Just have it.

987
01:20:20,970 --> 01:20:23,360
Left Vishuddhi.

988
01:20:23,360 --> 01:20:25,240
Call your mother here.

989
01:20:25,240 --> 01:20:38,850
Let her have a candle.

990
01:20:38,850 --> 01:20:46,030
Left hand towards me and right hand [on Mother 
Earth].

991
01:20:46,030 --> 01:20:51,480
What’s it Gavin?

992
01:20:51,480 --> 01:21:00,570
It’s quite a big thing.

993
01:21:00,570 --> 01:21:07,840
It’s so many pieces.

994
01:21:07,840 --> 01:21:14,760
I hope not you have spent so much money.

995
01:21:14,760 --> 01:21:27,950
You can say the mantra in your heart, “Mother 
I am not guilty."

996
01:21:27,950 --> 01:21:39,290
First [for] your mother, just give her this 
candle.

997
01:21:39,290 --> 01:21:40,360
What’s that?

998
01:21:40,360 --> 01:21:41,430
Oh Gavin!

999
01:21:41,430 --> 01:21:43,030
Beautiful isn’t it?

1000
01:21:43,030 --> 01:21:44,030
And a dolphin there!

1001
01:21:44,030 --> 01:21:45,030
Just imagine!

1002
01:21:45,030 --> 01:21:48,350
Thank you very much it’s beautiful.

1003
01:21:48,350 --> 01:21:50,750
It’s beautiful.

1004
01:21:50,750 --> 01:21:55,550
It’s very, very beautiful.

1005
01:21:55,550 --> 01:21:56,750
Beautiful.

1006
01:21:56,750 --> 01:22:01,550
Thank you very much.

1007
01:22:01,550 --> 01:22:02,750
Haa!

1008
01:22:02,750 --> 01:22:07,550
Gavin Brown: It’s French.

1009
01:22:07,550 --> 01:22:12,350
Shri Mataji: It’s French?

1010
01:22:12,350 --> 01:22:15,390
Why not get something English from English?

1011
01:22:15,390 --> 01:22:16,390
Alright.

1012
01:22:16,390 --> 01:22:18,130
It’s alright.

1013
01:22:18,130 --> 01:22:21,780
For me it’s alright.

1014
01:22:21,780 --> 01:22:22,780
Aha.

1015
01:22:22,780 --> 01:22:32,080
Working out!

1016
01:22:32,080 --> 01:22:41,460
Better?

1017
01:22:41,460 --> 01:22:46,210
Cancer patients should be treated with this, 
those who have got cancer or anything left-sided,

1018
01:22:46,210 --> 01:22:48,410
psychosomatic.

1019
01:22:48,410 --> 01:22:52,440
The other day, doctor – you will be amazed 
– there was a lady who came, she had cancer

1020
01:22:52,440 --> 01:22:57,870
of the glands and she had tied up her head 
with a scarf, in Madras.

1021
01:22:57,870 --> 01:23:02,160
So while talking I told her, “You take a 
candle and sit there with your left hand towards

1022
01:23:02,160 --> 01:23:05,960
me and right hand outside."

1023
01:23:05,960 --> 01:23:08,280
And after ten minutes I said, “Alright, 
remove your scarf."

1024
01:23:08,280 --> 01:23:14,370
The whole thing was cured.

1025
01:23:14,370 --> 01:23:17,290
It’s tremendous.

1026
01:23:17,290 --> 01:23:25,820
And they have now started that PhD thing in 
India.

1027
01:23:25,820 --> 01:23:31,930
Better?

1028
01:23:31,930 --> 01:23:44,140
Much better.

1029
01:23:44,140 --> 01:23:56,120
It’s working out.

1030
01:23:56,120 --> 01:24:01,730
Good.

1031
01:24:01,730 --> 01:24:19,390
(Shri Mataji talks to some children)

1032
01:24:19,390 --> 01:24:29,150
Akshay, you didn’t give me a kiss!

1033
01:24:29,150 --> 01:24:42,210
You must give me a kiss too!

1034
01:24:42,210 --> 01:24:49,100
Alright give it to Olympia then!

1035
01:24:49,100 --> 01:24:50,400
Feeling shy!

1036
01:24:50,400 --> 01:24:53,550
So I think I’ll take your leave Gavin.

1037
01:24:53,550 --> 01:24:54,650
Is it alright?

1038
01:24:54,650 --> 01:25:28,330
So tomorrow I don’t think you can come early 
in the morning, it’s too early – to the

1039
01:25:28,330 --> 01:25:33,220
airport.

1040
01:25:33,220 --> 01:25:58,620
And I’ll be leaving about seven o’clock 
from the house, at seven thirty-five I’ll

1041
01:25:58,620 --> 01:25:59,630
be there.

1042
01:25:59,630 --> 01:26:01,040
Are you alright now?

1043
01:26:01,040 --> 01:26:02,040
Good?

1044
01:26:02,040 --> 01:26:03,040
So where’s the baby?

1045
01:26:03,040 --> 01:26:04,040
Where’s Wendy’s baby?

1046
01:26:04,040 --> 01:26:05,530
Rodrigo Sanchez-Castro: It’s in Southampton 
Mother.

1047
01:26:05,530 --> 01:26:07,120
Shri Mataji: Oh I see.

1048
01:26:07,120 --> 01:26:11,520
So you want to have the name?

1049
01:26:11,520 --> 01:26:16,430
When was she born?

1050
01:26:16,430 --> 01:26:28,140
Rodrigo Sanchez-Castro: She was born on the 
thirteen of February.

1051
01:26:28,140 --> 01:26:33,310
Shri Mataji: So call her ‘Himakanya’.

1052
01:26:33,310 --> 01:26:42,330
Himakanya is the name of the Goddess born 
when…’Hima’ means ‘the snow’.

1053
01:26:42,330 --> 01:27:01,930
That’s the time she was born, when it was 
snowing.

1054
01:27:01,930 --> 01:27:12,790
Rodrigo Sanchez-Castro: It’s a boy Mother.

1055
01:27:12,790 --> 01:27:15,780
Shri Mataji: No.

1056
01:27:15,780 --> 01:27:17,780
Then ‘Himanshu’.

1057
01:27:17,780 --> 01:27:20,770
‘Himanshu’ is alright.

1058
01:27:20,770 --> 01:27:23,770
It’s a boy.

1059
01:27:23,770 --> 01:27:27,170
I thought it’s a girl they said.

1060
01:27:27,170 --> 01:27:29,430
Rodrigo Sanchez-Castro: No, no.

1061
01:27:29,430 --> 01:27:31,690
It’s a boy Mother.

1062
01:27:31,690 --> 01:27:34,520
Shri Mataji: Alright, so ‘Himanshu’.

1063
01:27:34,520 --> 01:27:35,650
It’s good.

1064
01:27:35,650 --> 01:27:37,660
‘Himanshu’ is a good name.

1065
01:27:37,660 --> 01:27:47,890
‘Himanshu’ means ‘the one who is born 
out of the..’ ‘anshu’ means ‘the essence’

1066
01:27:47,890 --> 01:27:50,030
‘Hima’ means ‘the ice’.

1067
01:27:50,030 --> 01:27:51,940
He’s the essence of the ice.

1068
01:27:51,940 --> 01:27:52,940
‘Himanshu’.

1069
01:27:52,940 --> 01:27:54,650
Is the name of Shiva.

1070
01:27:54,650 --> 01:28:02,400
